02/06/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- This week's visit by chief UN prosecutor Carla del Ponte is related to the transfer of war crimes cases to Croatian courts, Assistant Justice Minister Jaksa Muljacic said Tuesday (1 June).
Del Ponte's main objective is to inspect the work and organisation of local courts, Muljacic said.
He added that the talks, due to start Friday, would also focus on the country's improving co-operation with the tribunal.
(Vecernji List, Vjesnik - 02/06/04;
HINA - 01/06/04)
